               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17890708-52-person506">
                  JOHN
                   MORGAN
               <interp inst="t17890708-52-person506" type="surname" value="MORGAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890708-52-person506" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890708-52-person506" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>On Saturday last the prisoner brought this spoon to me to pledge; I never saw her before, it was in Blackfriars, she would not give any account; we took it to Mr. Hudson's on the Saturday afternoon.</p>
               <p>(The spoon deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I believe it to be my spoon I cannot swear to it.</p>
               <p>Mr. Peatt. You have a great many spoons? - I have.</p>
               <p>There is wrote upon it, Grand Hotel? - The Hotel is above; here is a griffin; I suppose I bought it second hand; the Prisoner was in my service at the time.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17890708-52-verdict259" type="verdictDescription">
